WEBVTT

00:02.496 --> 00:04.758
Hurry,
hurry, sit down, come in!

00:04.760 --> 00:07.089
I have the most fantastic news!

00:07.091 --> 00:08.751
What, did
Bub finally die?

00:08.871 --> 00:10.025
Who's Bub?

00:10.027 --> 00:12.493
My mother, and before
you make some snotty comment,

00:12.495 --> 00:15.658
yes I have a mother, do you
want to hear my news or not?!

00:15.660 --> 00:18.258
Yeah, if you're done
yelling at me for no reason.

00:18.260 --> 00:23.194
Last night, an Air Force B-52
bomber crashed off the coast of Bermuda!

00:23.196 --> 00:26.250
Well it's
about frickin time!

00:26.488 --> 00:29.634
What, we're we not bombing them in
advance of an amphibious invasion?

00:29.636 --> 00:30.934
Why would we invade.

00:30.936 --> 00:32.067
Bermuda.

00:32.069 --> 00:35.468
Ah, Bermuda. I
was thinking Bahamas.

00:35.470 --> 00:36.302
Same question.

00:36.304 --> 00:39.171
Same answer, Why not? It's
how we got the Virgin Islands.

00:39.173 --> 00:42.741
Actually, the United States
bought the Virgin Islands from Denmark.

00:42.743 --> 00:45.043
- Okay, Mr. Peabody...
- Are you finished?

00:45.045 --> 00:46.177
Yes.

00:46.179 --> 00:47.848
Good. Because the B-52 was -

00:47.968 --> 00:50.547
In the middle of
the Bermuda Triangle, is this

00:50.549 --> 00:53.282
about the Bermuda Triangle, because
that's my fourth biggest fear!

00:53.284 --> 00:56.017
It's about
the B-52's payload!

00:56.019 --> 00:57.685
Namely, a Mark-28

00:57.687 --> 00:59.052
hydrogen bomb.

00:59.054 --> 01:00.520
Ohhhh!

01:00.522 --> 01:03.088
Which ISIS...
is going to recover.

01:03.090 --> 01:04.188
What!?

01:04.190 --> 01:08.624
And then give to the U.S.
government in exchange for a huge reward!

01:08.626 --> 01:11.026
So, ransom it back.

01:11.028 --> 01:16.463
No, not ransom it, Cyril, we're-
look, semantics, whatever, this is -

01:16.465 --> 01:17.063
Treason?

01:17.065 --> 01:19.665
A huge
opportunity for ISIS!

01:19.667 --> 01:25.705
- Or the Russians...- The B-52 is
on the ocean floor here, at a depth

01:25.707 --> 01:27.174
of eight thousand feet...

01:27.176 --> 01:28.509
or thirteen hundred

01:28.511 --> 01:29.643
thirty-three fathoms.

01:29.645 --> 01:30.844
How do you know that?

01:30.846 --> 01:31.612
How do you not?

01:31.614 --> 01:34.714
So recovering the bomb
requires a deep submergence

01:34.716 --> 01:39.486
vehicle. The only American DSV is here,
in the Pacific. The Russians have

01:39.488 --> 01:42.989
one in the North Atlantic, so if
they hear about the wreck and start

01:42.991 --> 01:46.860
- steaming toward it-
- They don't actually steam anymore, Mother.

01:46.862 --> 01:50.029
It's a figure of speech,
like "shut your hatch,"

01:50.031 --> 01:54.635
because my point was, the Russians will
beat them to it. So we are going to

01:54.637 --> 01:57.037
beat the Russians.

01:57.039 --> 01:59.273
Give it up, folks!

01:59.275 --> 02:01.007
Mike Eruzione!

02:01.009 --> 02:05.244
LANA; Well - shut up - since
Krieger doesn't have a

02:05.246 --> 02:10.282
- submersible hidden in his lab...
- Or do I?

02:10.283 --> 02:12.317
I don't, actually.

02:12.319 --> 02:15.519
Then how are we supposed to
beat anybody to a hydrogen bomb, under

02:15.521 --> 02:17.987
two-point-two-seven
leagues of water?!

02:17.989 --> 02:21.222
Oh my Jesus
God damn alright already!

02:21.224 --> 02:22.623
Can I
possibly help you?

02:22.625 --> 02:25.191
Please, I know
you were talking loud so

02:25.193 --> 02:27.793
I'd hear you, so whatever, but
we're not speaking so if you

02:27.795 --> 02:32.764
want a deep submergence whatever you can
talk to my stupid gross brother Cecil!

02:32.766 --> 02:35.032
Who, by the way, is
here to see you.

02:35.034 --> 02:36.934
Ms. Archer will see you now.

02:36.936 --> 02:39.168
Thank you, Cheryl, I-
Rrraaaghh!

02:39.170 --> 02:41.837
I hate you!

02:41.839 --> 02:43.773
Hello, I'm Cecil Tunt.

02:43.775 --> 02:46.175
I believe you're in need
of some assistance?

02:46.877 --> 02:50.712
Yeah, RienPoortvliet just called,
he wants you to pose for him.

02:50.714 --> 02:54.081
C'mon, beloved
illustrator of "Gnomes"?

02:54.083 --> 02:56.883
Jesus, read a
coffee table book!

